<item>
            <title>[LU-12841] Add ability for lctl get_param to get subfield of YAML output</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12841</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to allow &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl get_param&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to extract a subfield from a YAML-formatted output instead of having to use &lt;tt&gt;awk&lt;/tt&gt;/&lt;tt&gt;cut&lt;/tt&gt;/&lt;tt&gt;grep&lt;/tt&gt; to extract these fields. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl get_param &lt;em&gt;PARAM&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;em&gt;KEY&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and/or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl get_param &amp;#45;k &lt;em&gt;KEY&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;PARAM&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; would work to print only the associated value for &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;em&gt;KEY&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.  There are not currently any parameters that contain a &apos;&lt;tt&gt;:&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
